{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"27884d42-af43-4701-9c07-a310b025afa8","content":"Here are common web API templates and auth options:\n\n**Templates**\n- **ASP.NET Core Web API** (`dotnet new webapi`) — most popular for C#/.NET\n- **Express.js** (`express-generator`) — Node.js\n- **FastAPI** / **Flask** / **Django REST** — Python\n- **Spring Boot** — Java\n\n**Authentication Options (ASP.NET Core example)**\n| Option | Use Case |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps, microservices |\n| **OAuth2 / OpenID Connect** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.) |\n| **Cookie-based** | Traditional server-rendered + API |\n| **API Keys** | Simple service-to-service |\n| **Microsoft Identity Platform** | Azure AD / Entra ID integration |\n\nFor `dotnet new webapi`, you can specify auth with:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # local accounts + JWT\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Azure AD single-tenant\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg     # Azure AD multi-tenant\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific project? If so, let me know your preferred language/framework and auth type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"de4e5aab-0616-409d-8b62-9a2dd2f0ffaf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":362,"requestId":"9C0E:1ED388:1CB0291:20249C2:6A07BF5A"},"id":"71883c98-7b2d-471c-9895-c4fd5bf29ff9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:50:45.336Z","parentId":"9edaac79-ab9d-436d-ba9e-2a56356a81de"}
